title: Prep roundup: Weir, Sauk Centre sweep Minnewaska

Join the Conversation To find out more about Facebook commenting please read the Conversation Guidelines and FAQs Prep roundup: Weir, Sauk Centre sweep Minnewaska TIMES STAFF REPORT 11:17 p.m. CDT October 19, 2015 Volleyball 14 CONNECT 1 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
SAUK CENTRE — Becca Weir led Sauk Centre with 15 kills and three blocks as the Mainstreeters rolled to a sweep over Minnewaska in West Central Conference high school volleyball action Monday. 
Game scores were 25-12, 25-17, 25-11. 
Taylor Borgerding added nine kills, Jill Klaphake had 33 set assists and nine digs and Morgan Gamradt had 12 digs and three ace serves for Sauk Centre. 
The Mainstreeters, receiving votes in the latest Class 2A poll, remain unbeaten in the West Central at 13-0 and improve to 23-3 overall. 
BBE 3, ALBANY 0 
ALBANY — Ashley Trustheim finished with 10 kills to lead Belgrade-Brooten-Elrosa past Albany in a nonconference match. 
Game scores were 25-20, 25-17, 25-22. 
Erin Navratil led the Huskies (18-7 overall) with 11 kills, Valerie Parker had 27 set assists and Sidnet Schiffler finished with 24 digs. 
MILACA 3, ONAMIA 0 
ONAMIA — Ellie Banks led Milaca with 11 kills in a nonconference sweep of Onamia. 
Game scores were 25-18, 25-20, 28-26. 
Claire Mettling added 14 digs for the Wolves (9-16). 
NYA 3, KIMBALL 2 
KIMBALL — Madison Hurrle finished with 18 kills and 19 digs for Kimball, but the Cubs dropped the nonconference match to Norwood Young America. 
Game scores were 22-25, 24-26, 25-22, 25-21, 15-13. 
Emma Kuechle had nine kills for Kimball and Kari Schiefelbein added 15 digs. 
ADAPTED SOCCER 
NORTH SUBURBAN 6, 
ST. CLOUD 5 
CIRCLE PINES — North Suburban scored twice late, including the game-winning goal in the final minute, to slip past St. Cloud. 
Jordan Williams led St. Cloud with two goals and two assists and Tyrell Franck-Cross added a goal and two assists for the Thunder (3-2).
